## 9. Risk Factors

- **Industry-specific risks:** Construction cyclicality and pronounced seasonality in the Tahoe Basin (short building season); exposure to landfill tipping-fee inflation; possible local permitting/franchise constraints on roll-off service that should be confirmed.
- **Financial risks:** No disclosed multi-year financials — growth trend, margin stability, and working-capital profile are all unverified. "Cash Flow" is presented as a single SDE-style figure; a true EBITDA (post fair-market owner compensation) will likely be lower than $400K.
- **Operational risks:** Small headcount (est. 5–8 FTE) creates key-person and driver-availability risk; aging or limited fleet (1 truck) caps capacity and may require capex.
- **Regulatory / legal:** Confirm CalRecycle / county solid-waste hauler permitting, DOT/FMCSA registration for trucks, and that roll-off service is not encumbered by the residential franchise agreements held by STR / TTSD.
- **Deal-specific conditions:**
  - **Obtain the asking price from the broker** — the deal cannot be screened on valuation until then (Buy Box #5 and rubric line 8 are currently un-scorable).
  - Reconcile SDE vs. EBITDA — re-underwrite at a normalized EBITDA after market owner pay.
  - Confirm 10+ years in business and obtain a trailing-3-year P&L to validate the growth requirement.
  - Confirm customer concentration; if the largest customer ≥20%, seller financing should be required.

